original: Eukaryotes are believed to have diverged from archaea, followed by endosymbiotic events with bacteria that led to the formation of mitochondria and chloroplasts. These organelles are now integral components of modern eukaryotic cells. The major lineages of eukaryotes began to diversify during the Precambrian period, approximately 1.5 billion years ago.
